---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import { GITHUB_URL } from '../consts';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Who I am and what this blog is."
	pubDate={new Date('Jun 01 2026')}
>
	<p>
		I'm Hampton Copeland — a chemist and a compulsive thinker, and a graduate student in Tennessee
		wrapping up a master's in theoretical chemistry. My thesis is on relativistic calculations of
		X-ray scattering.
	</p>

	<p>
		Chemistry comes first for me, but I'm wired to look forward — at where the science, the tools,
		and the technology are all headed next. Alongside the thesis I take on computational-chemistry
		and drug-discovery projects, and I keep a home lab as a tool and a sandbox (this site is served
		from it, fittingly).
	</p>

	<p>
		I grew up a farmer, and I've built more than a few drag and street cars — so I got here by way
		of wrenches and dirt long before keyboards. That's probably why I'd rather understand how a
		thing actually works than take the brochure's word for it.
	</p>

	<p>
		Plenty of what I do doesn't obviously track to the rest of it, and I've stopped trying to force
		it into one tidy story. This blog is the same: anything on my mind — some chemistry, some of the
		future I can't stop thinking about, some of it neither. I'd rather write the post I wish I'd
		found than the one that ranks. Find me on
		<a href={GITHUB_URL} rel="me noopener" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
